iraqi police subjected to attack west of baghdad
baghdad , january 22 / xinhua / the iraqi police announced today , thursday , that unknown armed men attacked iraqi policemen in the city of falluja , west of baghdad , and inflicted many casualties among them , according to what the arabia satellite channel reported .
the channel quoted an officer in the iraqi police as saying , " there was an attack on the iraqi police , which caused many casualties " , and added that the attack took place on the highway between the cities of falluja and ramadi , west of baghdad .
no further information was available about the incident .
in a separate incident , the qatari satellite channel al-jazeera said today , thursday , that two iraqi security guards were killed and another was wounded as a result of firing last night , wednesday , after a member of an american patrol suspected movements inside a car showroom in the city of falluja , west of baghdad .
the channel said that traces of the firing were apparent on the cars in the showroom , whose glass was shattered and the iraqi police rushed to the place of the incident to investigate .
death of a person in thailand suspected of being infected with birds ' influenza
bangkok , 23 january / xinhua / sudarat kiforafan , the thai health minister , reported that a thai , suspected of being infected with birds influenza , died in the evening of today , friday .
in a conversation with the local itv television , the minister mentioned that a person died in chachoengsao this evening and that it was not verified so far whether or not the cause of death was infection with birds influenza .
the man , who is a butcher in his fifties , was one of the suspected patients infected with birds influenza . the laboratory test has not verified so far whether or not he was infected with the disease .
thailand had confirmed this afternoon , friday , that two children who showed symptoms of pulmonary infections were infected with birds influenza and that the h5n1 virus , which causes the outbreak of the disease , was discovered in some chicken farms in central thailand .
, sumachai perabacorn the acting representative of the world health organization in thailand told the xinhua news agency that this was the first time the birds influenza disease has been transmitted between humans and chickens .
in case of confirmation that the death was caused by the birds influenza , this person will become the first mortality caused by the disease in thailand .
the disease caused the death of five people in vietnam .
controlling the cracking of a dam in north west china
wulumuqi , january 23 / xinhua / more than two thousand members of the army , armed police force and the militias undertook during the last two days the restoration of a 60 - meter wide crack in a dam in the xinjiang self - rule region of the weiwuer nationality in northwest china .
chang ching li , leader of the production and reconstruction commission in shingiang , said that by ten o'clock this evening , the speed of the flow of water slowed down from the reservoir known by the name of " bayi " or the " first of august " to 30 cubic meters per second and the water level in the reservoir fell to 2.4 meters .
chang said , " it was possible to control the situation " .
the crack in the dam took place wednesday night , on the eve of the new traditional lunar chinese year .
now , the evacuation and housing is virtually completed of all the inhabitants exposed to danger , whose number was 13,800 persons .
no news has been reported about casualties , although the waters flooded eight companies affiliated with the shingiang commission .
it is worth mentioning that the dam was built in the year 1957 with a storage capacity of 30 million cubic meters .
a committee from the state center for controlling floods and relief from droughts arrived at the areas struck by the flood .
jordanian monarch returns to amman from davos
amman , january 24 / xinhua / the jordanian monarch , king abdullah the second returned this evening , saturday , to amman after participating in the meeting of the world economic forum in davos .
the jordanian monarch delivered a political speech in front of the forum , in which he focused on the necessity for all sectors in the arab world to confront such issues as a regime that responds to the aspirations of its people and adopts transparency , an educational system dedicated to achieve distinction and an active private sector that can exploit the huge capabilities of the region .
also , the jordanian monarch held several meetings with a number of leaders and officials alongside the forum .
in a meeting with governors of the healthcare sector , the jordanian monarch expressed his interest in attracting international companies to invest in the jordanian pharmaceuticals industry , to help jordanian pharmaceutical companies acquire scientific and technical knowledge and innovation , or through allowing jordanian companies to participate in the manufacture of some of the products of international pharmaceutical companies .
united states lifts tuna fish ban imposed on el salvador
mexico city , january 24 / xinhua / the united states lifted the ban on importing tuna fish it imposed in the year 1994 on el salvador , after reports confirmed that the country in central america had ceased using fishing nets that form a threat to dolphins .
reports received here today , saturday , said that the united states was convinced that el salvador had completed the requirements for protecting dolphins in the pacific ocean and respecting the laws of the tuna fish tropical committee between the two americas .
douglas barclay , the american ambassador to el salvador announced the end of the ban on importing tuna fish , adding that it " would provide new trade opportunities for companies specialized in this industry . "
the united states imports tuna fish only from mexico , ecuador and el salvador , the size of whose production amounts to 20 thousand tons annually .
philippines army rejects call to assume government
manila , january 25 / xinhua / the philippines armed forces rejected today , sunday , a call presented by a group for the army to temporarily assume the leadership of the government because of the expected crisis .
the chief of the general information bureau of the philippines armed forces , lieutenant colonel daniel locero , said that the measure proposed by the citizens ' committee for the national crisis , which said that it represents a large sector of the society , violates the constitution of the country .
locero said , " the philippines armed forces will not think of this proposal .
this proposal incites the soldiers to overthrow the government , which is a matter considered to be a violation to the constitution " .
in an open letter , he said that the group had urged the chief of staff of the philippines armed forces , general narcisso abaya to take the government 's affairs in his hand because those who aspire to assume the presidency ( in the may elections ) and the political parties had failed to discuss the real and vital programs that tear the nation .
also , the group presented an urgent program , the implementation of which the philippines armed forces could discuss during the proposed assumption of power .
locero said that the military establishment , consisting of 113 thousands soldiers , would continue to support the constitutional government and would abide by the principles stipulated in the constitution .
he called on the group to help the army stay far away from any policies .
israeli sources say washington likely to approve disengagement plan
