new reserve in shengli oil field exceeds 100 million tons
jinan , january 28 / the xinhua reporter learned recently from shengli oilfield in the shandong province in east china that the recently confirmed oil reserve in the field reached 113.01 million tons in the year 2003 , thus raising the confirmed oil reserve in this old field by 100 million tons annually for 21 continuous years .
an official in the field said that out of this new reserve 356.18 millions tons are fit for extraction immediately .
in addition to that , scientists discovered in the field last year more than 200 million tons of unconfirmed reserves .
the official added that a large number of high and new technologies were used in work to develop the field last year , which led to the extraction of more high density petrol , and to discovering oil reserves that are easier to extract .
chicken slaughtering banned in markets in peking
peking , january 28 / xinhua / the slaughtering of chicken and the selling of untested meat and chicken products was banned in peking today , wednesday . it is an emergency measure taken by the local government to make the capital safe against the transfer of the bird flu virus to it .
yesterday , tuesday , it was confirmed that the virus is the reason for the death of ducks in the self ruled guangxi region of the zhuang nationality south of china .
leo gian , deputy director of the industry and trade office in peking municipality , announced here today , wednesday , stricter control and inspection steps to prevent the entry of chicken products incoming from other localities to peking .
leo said that the food safety office in peking municipality must be notified immediately of cases of bird flu virus , and that those who delay notification will be severely punished .
statistics issued by the local government show that there are 139 farms for raising chicken , 63 markets , 36 supermarkets , and 31 slaughterhouses for slaughtering chicken in peking .
no chicken products coming from countries infected with the bird flu disease , such as the korean republic , vietnam , japan and thailand were found in the local markets so far .
inspection operations of chicken products available in peking during the spring festival showed that these products are free from the bird flu and safe as food , according to an official at the food safety office .
conclusion of joint military maneuvers between yemen and the united states
sana'a , january 28 / xinhua / yemeni sources said that units of the yemeni and american coast guard troops concluded today , wednesday , joint military maneuvers in aden bay .
the sources said that these joint military maneuvers between yemen and the united states included training in confronting terrorist operations that might target ships , but they did not reveal any details on the maneuvers .
the sources pointed out that early next march yemen will receive eight boats for the coastal unit after a yemeni team concluded training on it in the united states last month as part of the yemeni plan aimed at enhancing coast guard operations and preventing smuggling into the country from neighboring countries .
it is worth mentioning that the united states is linked with yemen by an agreement to fight terrorism and offers the necessary aid to yemen to form an effective coast guard force to protect the yemeni beaches , at a length of 2,500 kilometers from its borders with the sultanate of oman on the arab sea , to the saudi borders on the red sea .
blair accepts hutton 's report in full
london , january 28 / xinhua / british prime minister tony blair said today , wednesday , that he accepted lord hutton 's report which cleared him of any crime in the suicide of weapons expert david kelly last year .
blair said before parliament , following the publishing of the results of lord hutton 's report , " the allegations saying that i or anyone else lied to this council on purpose and misled the country by falsifying intelligence reports on weapons of mass destruction are the essence of lies . "
the prime minister said he is " extremely grateful " to brian hutton , british high court of justice , who published a report on the results of his investigations into the killing of kelly an hour ago .
blair said amid heated applause from the members of the labor party to which he belongs " the report is considered an extraordinarily comprehensive , detailed and clear report and does not leave any room for skepticism or interpretation .
we accept this report in full " .
he stressed that there was no " dishonest strategy to leak the name of dr. kelly " .
blair called on all who accused him of lying in the iraqi matter to withdraw their allegations .
blair said , " i demand simply from those who started this allegation and repeated it all these months to withdraw it now honestly , clearly and fully . "
zimbabwe urged to enhance relations with china
harare , january 28 / xinhua / a zimbabwe official stressed here today the necessity of his country taking advantage of the wide possibilities of the chinese market in order to reduce the effect of the sanctions imposed by the western countries on zimbabwe .
saviour kasoquer , president of the defense and interior committee in parliament , made this statement during the presentation of a report to parliament on the visit by a delegation of his committee to china .
kasoquer said , " china provides the opportunity for zimbabwe to establish cooperation with a friendly country prepared to offer help . "
jiles motsikwa , member of parliament for the motari north region of the opposition democratic change movement , had visited china in the company of kasoquer during the period between last october 22 and 27 .
there are still possibilities to establish joint companies to provide more job opportunities to transport technology and the added value to zimbabwe products , according to the official .
it is noted that zimbabwe and china enjoy strong relations whose history goes back to the days of the struggle for independence in the african state .
2,500 afghani refugees return to their country this year
kabul , january 29 / xinhua / the spokesperson for the united nations , manuel di almieda da silva , said here today that 2,500 afghani refugees from eight countries , especially iran , have returned to their country up until now in the year 2004 .
he said during a press conference that the refugees , among them one thousand survivors of the destructive earthquake that hit the city of bam east of iran , have returned to afghanistan with the help of the united nations high commission for refugees .
the spokesperson said , " the high commission for refugees will continue helping the afghanis who survived bam 's earthquake to return as long as they want to go back , " adding that the commission offered the necessary food and complete heating for those who arrived to the crossing point in herat .
on the other hand , 50 refugees from another seven countries were returned with the help of the commission .
more than 2.2 million afghani refugees returned to their country at the start of the operation to return refugees at the beginning of 2002 , facilitated by the commission . more than 252 thousand others returned from iran in the same period .
disappointment in al-naqab prison after returning 43 palestinian prisoners to jail
gaza , january 29 / xinhua / tens of palestinian detainees were disappointed after israeli prison authorities announced writing the names of 37 palestinian prisoners in desert al-naqab prison , south of israel , off the list of those to be released today , thursday .
a number of palestinian prisoners said that prison authorities had returned yesterday 37 prisoners who were scheduled to be released today . they also returned today 16 other prisoners , without mentioning the reasons behind writing off the names .
palestinian detainee hani abu nahel said in a telephone call from his prison with the new chinese news agency xinhua , " the situation of the palestinian detainees is very difficult after israeli prison authorities released a small number of detainees as part of the exchange deal . "
abu nahel said , " prison authorities took us out today in preparation for releasing us , but they returned me and 42 detainees with me , and informed us our names were written off the list of those to be released . "
detainee abdullah anjas from ramallah said , " israeli wardens want to play with the nerves of detainees , some of whom cry due to the difficult circumstances they went through . " he stressed that most of the released had short prison sentences and had only a short time left to remain in jail . "
